&lt;p&gt;OK, I marked this ticket as resolved for 1.1.1. Thank you for keeping track! &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17646350" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2022 22:21:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that while it is true that &lt;tt&gt;JavaCryptoRandom&lt;/tt&gt; extends &lt;tt&gt;Random&lt;/tt&gt; and does not need to; an app casting&#160;a&#160;&lt;tt&gt;CryptoRandom&lt;/tt&gt; to a &lt;tt&gt;Random&lt;/tt&gt; is IMO out of bounds and unsupported since it is not documented and the app has to force the cast. This was not the intended use case anyway. The next release will not extend &lt;tt&gt;Random&lt;/tt&gt; and still maintain binary compatibility since the class is package-private.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
